  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the various non-tech companies that visit N.S.I.T for placements and what is the skill set that they are looking for in a person?",
  "response": "Netaji Subhas Institute of Technology (NSIT), now known as NSUT (Netaji Subhas University of Technology), is a reputable engineering college in India that attracts a wide range of companies for campus placements, including non-tech companies. While the companies visiting can vary each year, several sectors typically recruit from NSIT:\n\n1. **Consulting Firms:**\n   - Companies like McKinsey & Company, Boston Consulting Group (BCG), Bain & Company, Deloitte, KPMG, and PwC often look for analytical and problem-solving skills, effective communication, teamwork, and a good understanding of business fundamentals.\n\n2. **Financial Services:**\n   - Banks and financial institutions like Goldman Sachs, JPMorgan Chase, Barclays, and American Express look for candidates with strong quantitative skills, financial modeling abilities, attention to detail, and an understanding of financial instruments.\n\n3. **FMCG (Fast-Moving Consumer Goods):**\n   - Companies such as Hindustan Unilever, Procter & Gamble, ITC, and Nestl\u00e9 may seek students with marketing acumen, analytical skills, creativity, and an understanding of consumer behavior.\n\n4. **Manufacturing and Operations:**\n   - Organizations like Tata Steel, Maruti Suzuki, and Larsen & Toubro focus on candidates with strong analytical and quantitative abilities, problem-solving skills, and knowledge of operations and supply chain management.\n\n5. **Retail:**\n   - Companies in the retail sector, such as Reliance Retail, might look for skills in data analysis, customer relationship management, and an understanding of retail operations.\n\n**Skill Sets Valued by Non-Tech Companies:**\n\n1. **Analytical and Problem-Solving Skills:**\n   - Ability to analyze data critically and develop practical solutions to problems.\n\n2. **Communication Skills:**\n   - Strong verbal and written communication abilities to convey ideas effectively.\n\n3. **Teamwork and Leadership:**\n   - Proven ability to work collaboratively in teams and take initiative when leading group projects.\n\n4. **Business Acumen:**\n   - Understanding of basic business principles and how businesses operate, which is particularly important for consulting and financial roles.\n\n5. **Attention to Detail:**\n   - Precise and detail-oriented approach, particularly valuable in finance and consulting roles.\n\n6. **Adaptability:**\n   - Ability to adapt to different roles and environments, learning quickly on the job.\n\n7. **Quantitative Skills:**\n   - Strong mathematical foundation for roles involving data analysis or financial modeling.\n\nStudents should also focus on internships, relevant projects, and building a strong CV to enhance their employability in these sectors. Engagement in extracurricular activities and networking can further bolster their profiles.",
